central elementary school, also known as the first and second new bern academy, is a historic elementary school building located at new bern, craven county, north carolina. it was built about 1806, and is a two-story, brick building with a hipped roof and two interior ridge chimneys. it features a semicircular tetrastyle entrance porch with tuscan order columns and a roof cupola. it has a rear addition dated to the late-19th century. it was listed on the national register of historic places in 1972.